text.section:
If voluntary efforts to reduce excess capacity prove insufficient, as a last resort the Maryland Health Care Commission and the Health Services Cost Review Commission may petition the Secretary to delicense any hospital or part of a hospital or hospital service based on a finding after a public hearing that the delicensure is consistent with the State health plan or institution-specific plan. The petition shall specify in detail all efforts made by the petitioner to encourage the hospital:
To reduce its underutilized capacity;
To merge or consolidate;
To become more efficient and effective; and
To convert from acute capacity to alternative uses, where appropriate.
